output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of all subjects now working in TRANSPORTATION AND STORAGE who studied in each region 5 years after graduation, male and female Level 7 (research) graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
output.maptext:
For Level 7 (research) graduates of all subjects in the TRANSPORTATION AND STORAGE industry 5 years after graduation, the region that saw the highest number of students
                    studying there was East of England . The region with the lowest number of students studying
                    there was West Midlands . The region with the highest number of graduates living
                    there 5 years after graduation was London  and the region with the
                    least graduates living there was East of England .
output.maptext2:
For Level 7 (research) graduates of all subjects in the TRANSPORTATION AND STORAGE industry, the region with the highest proportionate increase in graduates who studied there compared to living
                    there 5 years after graduation is London , where the number of
                    graduates increased by 155 %. The region with the largest
                    decrease is East of England where the number of graduates decreased by NA %.
